  "verdict": "data_limited (power-limited, honestly quantified) -- but the RIGHT product at last. PG.08 tests what PG.07 said was missing: real phase-connected ToA RESIDUALS (PuMA/IAR daily cadence, 969 post-glitch TOAs over three giant glitches), glitch model removed, refit-absorption basis projected out. Achieved reach: Vela-2021 1.83 periods (the public .tim starts at tau=10.0 d -- the live sub-day TOAs of Zubieta+2023 are not in the release, so Vela stays BELOW the 2.8 gate), J0742-2822 1.45, and J1740-3015 2.81 periods -- J1740-3015 is the FIRST real residual recovery to clear the ~2.8-period gate. omega=2.583 is NOT special in any leg (comb p = J0835-4510:0.28, J0742-2822:0.89, J1740-3015:0.48; lambda battery agrees). The end-to-end injection at the real sampling AND real noise quantifies what that non-detection is worth: at reference eps=0.30 the detection power is J0835-4510:0%, J0742-2822:17%, J1740-3015:50% (eps=0 false-positive ~0%) -- the sub-gate legs REPRODUCE the PG.06 range-blindness on real residuals, and even the gate-passing leg reaches only ~50% power at eps=0.30 (684 us RMS noise), formally 0/3 legs pass the >=60% validation bar. At the predicted eps~0.017 the power is 0% everywhere -- the amplitude wall stands. So PG.08 is a bounded statement: no comb, and a eps>~0.3 comb would have been seen with ~50% probability on J1740-3015; nothing stronger. Walled-clock reading on the released GLTD ladders: 0/2 timescale ratios near the 2.7095 bend (null), and ['J0835-4510'] resolve(s) >= 3 transient modes -- Vela-2021's 3-mode fit is a WALL exception to keep on record (PG.04c counted 45/46 <= 2). No claim; firewall intact. Decisive next: the sub-day live TOAs (IAR internal) or an equivalent public early-window release would push Vela past the gate where the eps sensitivity is best."
